What we're building this step
A form for the dev team to raise a request. Three things to decide before code:

The fields, mapped straight to the data model from last turn: title, pr_link, and an optional description. Notice what's not a field — the API this request is for (api_ref) comes from the page context (entity.metadata.name, since this page lives on chat-api's tab), and requested_by comes from the logged-in user. A good habit: never ask the user to type something the system already knows.

The "mode" idea. The dev-team section needs two views — a button to start, and the form itself. We model that with one piece of state, mode: 'list' | 'create'. The button flips it to 'create'; Submit/Cancel flips it back. This is the standard way to handle "show different things in the same spot."

Submission is local for now. On submit we'll push the new request into a React array and show it in a list. No backend yet — which means it disappears on refresh. That "disappears on refresh" pain is exactly the motivation for the DB next step, so it's worth feeling it.

The form component
