Diagnosed misplaced braces causing component to return void
Diagnosed misplaced braces causing component to return void
The error is a misplaced closing brace, and it's a great one to learn to read. Decode the message: its type '() => void' is not a valid JSX element type. TypeScript is saying ProductionRequestsPage is a function that returns nothing (void), but a component has to return JSX (a ReactNode).

Why does it return nothing? Look at where your braces fell — the const currentUser = ... line and the entire return (...) block ended up inside handleCreate. So handleCreate is the thing returning the JSX, and ProductionRequestsPage itself falls off the end with no return. The } that should close handleCreate right after setMode('list') is missing, so everything below got swallowed into it.

Two smaller bugs came along too: your import is a default import (import NewRequestInput from ...) but NewRequestInput is a named type export, and the form component isn't actually wired in yet — the API-team branch still has the old raw <button>.

