The principle to carry forward for Express handlers under these lint rules: res.json() / res.send() / res.status() are things you do, not things you return. The return; keyword is only there to stop the handler early so it doesn't keep executing and try to send a second response (which would crash with "headers already sent"). Keep those two ideas separate and you won't hit this rule again.

