How the prop slots map to the parts you were fighting:

InputProps.style styles the input box (the outlined container), so that's where the white background, rounding, and lift-shadow go. inputProps (lowercase — easy to miss) styles the actual <input>/<textarea> element, so the typed-text color goes there. InputLabelProps.style is the floating "Title *" label, and FormHelperTextProps.style is the helper line under each field. All four use style (inline), so none of them can be overridden by the theme.

After this you'll get white field boxes with a subtle shadow, dark labels, and dark typed text — clearly distinct from the gray panel.

