2. Return 200, not 409, for "wrong state" / "no match". GitLab retries webhooks on any non-2xx response — so the match.status !== 'pending_pr' and !result.ok branches will trigger retry storms when GitLab resends a duplicate merge event (which it does). Idempotency cases should look like accepted-and-ignored:

