Three small things worth knowing in the rare insert-after-issue-succeeded failure: this is a real consequence of "external side-effect before DB write." It almost never happens in practice (your DB is local; insert won't fail unless something's deeply wrong), but the surfaced orphanedIssueUrl in the response means you'd at least see which issue was left behind. For a POC this is fine. If it bothered you, the more elaborate fix is to close the issue automatically when the insert fails — but I'd punt that until you actually see it happen.

