Your notNullable schema means existing rows can't survive without those columns. Since the new fields live inside the createTable block, they only appear on fresh tables. If your dev DB was created before these columns existed, those columns won't be there and inserts will fail with a "no such column" error. Two options: wipe the DB (in-memory sqlite needs only a backend restart; a file means delete it), or add temp-migration blocks like you did for the manifest PR links — but you'd have to add them as nullable() first, since you can't add a notNullable column to a table with existing rows. For a POC the wipe is cleaner.

