if (req.header('x-gitlab-token') !== webhookSecret) {
  res.status(401).json({ error: 'invalid token' });
  return;
}
…and then the config key becomes required because GitLabClient.fromConfig (or wherever you read it) would call getString('webhookSecret'). Until that's in your code, the config key is unused dead weight.

For the POC right now, your webhook endpoint is open — anyone who finds the tunnel URL can POST a merge_request/action: merge payload and march a request forward. Fine for local dev; just don't forget to add the verification before the tunnel URL exists in any chat log or shared place. So: remove that line from app-config.yaml, restart, and you should clear the 503 (assuming the other configs are correct).

