Diagnosed HTTPS configuration issue and formulated solution
Diagnosed HTTPS configuration issue and formulated solution
That's the classic osixia/phpldapadmin gotcha: the image starts in HTTPS mode by default and refuses plain HTTP, so port 80 inside the container returns Forbidden when you map it to a host port and hit it over http://. Two fixes; I'd take the first.

Disable HTTPS for local dev — add one env var:

yaml
phpldapadmin:
  image: osixia/phpldapadmin:0.9.0
  container_name: phpldapadmin
  environment:
    PHPLDAPADMIN_LDAP_HOSTS: openldap
    PHPLDAPADMIN_HTTPS: "false"     # <-- add this
  ports:
    - "8082:80"
The container has to be recreated (not just restarted) for env-var changes to apply:

bash
docker compose down
docker compose up -d
Then http://localhost:8082 will give you the login screen.

Or keep HTTPS and map 443 instead:

yaml
ports:
  - "8082:443"
…and browse to https://localhost:8082, accepting the self-signed cert warning. Annoying for daily use, fine if you want HTTPS habits.

