Now, what credentials is for — this is the part that decides which one you drop:

credentials: true makes the browser send cookies and auth headers on cross-origin requests to your backend, and lets it read the response. Backstage uses this so your logged-in session token rides along with every /api/... call. Without it, cross-origin API calls go out with no auth → backend says 401 → you appear logged out even after logging in. So on a cross-origin setup, credentials is mandatory for auth to work.

